1
00:00:14,926 --> 00:00:19,195
We will now announce the lunch sales rankings...

2
00:00:19,196 --> 00:00:21,366
for the 1,000-dollar sales race.

3
00:00:22,002 --> 00:00:25,142
In 17th place, Everything About Tteokbokki.

4
00:00:26,006 --> 00:00:27,745
- Tteokbokki...
- No one is eating tteokbokki.

5
00:00:27,746 --> 00:00:30,116
- In 18th place, Sunlin.
- Even if it's cheap.

6
00:00:30,376 --> 00:00:31,376
Sunlin?

7
00:00:31,377 --> 00:00:33,946
In 19th place, Arirang House.

8
00:00:36,146 --> 00:00:38,286
And in last 20th place is...

9
00:00:38,886 --> 00:00:40,186
Agungi.

10
00:00:41,526 --> 00:00:42,725
Well done, everyone.

11
00:00:42,726 --> 00:00:44,896
(Agungi in the last 20th place)

12
00:00:46,496 --> 00:00:50,365
Even if we made our best dish...

13
00:00:50,366 --> 00:00:53,196
This is a survival game where that alone may not be enough.

14
00:00:53,466 --> 00:00:54,566
No one is eating tteokbokki.

15
00:00:54,936 --> 00:00:55,936
I know.

16
00:00:56,606 --> 00:00:59,105
People wanted a proper meal,

17
00:00:59,106 --> 00:01:01,076
but our dish didn't satisfy that.

18
00:01:01,376 --> 00:01:02,845
We can make so many dishes,

19
00:01:02,846 --> 00:01:04,316
but we made something we weren't familiar with.

20
00:01:04,946 --> 00:01:06,576
We need to sell something solid.

21
00:01:06,886 --> 00:01:08,516
We can't finish like this.

22
00:01:09,016 --> 00:01:10,056
I agree.

23
00:01:10,716 --> 00:01:13,185
We have 900 dollars left.

24
00:01:13,186 --> 00:01:15,155
- Okay.
- By spending more,

25
00:01:15,156 --> 00:01:17,356
we must come up with a survival strategy.

26
00:01:17,856 --> 00:01:19,696
If we keep selling the same way,

27
00:01:19,796 --> 00:01:21,166
we'll get eliminated.

28
00:01:21,396 --> 00:01:22,766
Let's go with what we do best.

29
00:01:23,896 --> 00:01:26,266
My strength is running a meat restaurant.

30
00:01:27,306 --> 00:01:30,106
I decided to bring out my signature menu,

31
00:01:30,276 --> 00:01:32,405
which is butter pork galbi.

32
00:01:32,406 --> 00:01:33,406
(Butter pork galbi)

33
00:01:33,407 --> 00:01:34,945
Since I'm good at pork galbi,

34
00:01:34,946 --> 00:01:36,346
we can make butter pork galbi with pork shoulder.

35
00:01:36,816 --> 00:01:37,816
We must survive.

36
00:01:38,016 --> 00:01:39,346
I'll survive no matter what.

37
00:01:41,146 --> 00:01:43,416
(Supermarket)

38
00:01:44,156 --> 00:01:46,986
We went to the supermarket and checked the meat.

39
00:01:47,156 --> 00:01:49,925
We bought all the pork shoulder and pork belly...

40
00:01:49,926 --> 00:01:51,696
in stock.

41
00:01:52,396 --> 00:01:54,096
- I'll take all of it.
- Okay.

42
00:01:55,966 --> 00:01:57,496
Are you changing the entire menu?

43
00:01:57,836 --> 00:01:58,836
Yes.

44
00:01:58,996 --> 00:02:00,706
You're changing the menu?

45
00:02:01,266 --> 00:02:03,936
That's a huge risk. You will make a serious loss.

46
00:02:04,576 --> 00:02:05,576
(Extra ingredient cost: 281.6 dollars)

47
00:02:05,577 --> 00:02:06,875
The total is...

48
00:02:06,876 --> 00:02:08,945
Even if it means going into the red,

49
00:02:08,946 --> 00:02:12,516
let's take a reckless challenge that only the loser can take.

50
00:02:13,716 --> 00:02:15,885
Since the meat was pre-cut...

51
00:02:15,886 --> 00:02:17,386
at the supermarket,

52
00:02:17,486 --> 00:02:20,186
I made knife marks to season it thoroughly.

53
00:02:21,426 --> 00:02:24,056
I made the marinade with soy sauce, mirin,

54
00:02:24,196 --> 00:02:27,326
Cheongju, crushed garlic, sesame oil, and sugar.

55
00:02:29,296 --> 00:02:30,366
We can do this.

56
00:02:31,696 --> 00:02:34,105
It's an instant marinade. About 30 minutes should be enough.

57
00:02:34,106 --> 00:02:35,106
Okay.

58
00:02:35,906 --> 00:02:37,276
(After 30 minutes)

59
00:02:39,876 --> 00:02:42,205
I started thinking,

60
00:02:42,206 --> 00:02:45,176
"How do we make this even better for customers?"

61
00:02:45,876 --> 00:02:47,015
There's a grill grate.

62
00:02:47,016 --> 00:02:48,186
Oh, nice.

63
00:02:48,716 --> 00:02:50,116
Shall we use it as a heat sink?

64
00:02:50,716 --> 00:02:52,686
Why don't we grill the meat on top of it?

65
00:02:53,316 --> 00:02:56,386
It's strange how the idea even came to me.

66
00:02:56,726 --> 00:02:58,395
If we just grill the meat directly,

67
00:02:58,396 --> 00:03:00,425
the sauce would drip through the holes.

68
00:03:00,426 --> 00:03:02,426
Then the holes would be blocked.

69
00:03:02,566 --> 00:03:04,996
So we used a steamer rack as a guard.

70
00:03:05,696 --> 00:03:09,035
Grilling meat over direct flame gives it...

71
00:03:09,036 --> 00:03:11,606
an amazing mix of sweetness and smoky aroma.

72
00:03:12,136 --> 00:03:15,246
To make it look more generous,

73
00:03:15,376 --> 00:03:17,875
I finely chopped fishcake for tteokbokki,

74
00:03:17,876 --> 00:03:18,876
deep-fried it,

75
00:03:20,546 --> 00:03:22,546
- and plated it on the side.
- Okay.

76
00:03:23,616 --> 00:03:26,826
(Butter pork galbi, 19 dollars)

77
00:03:27,626 --> 00:03:31,356
And our original lunch dish, Shanghai vermicelli tteokbokki.

78
00:03:32,256 --> 00:03:36,166
(Shanghai vermicelli tteokbokki and butter pork galbi, 26 dollars)

79
00:03:36,326 --> 00:03:39,366
Butter pork galbi will be on one side on the plate.

80
00:03:41,706 --> 00:03:44,376
We created an image with AI in a hurry.

81
00:03:44,736 --> 00:03:47,576
We even had the poster specially made.

82
00:03:48,376 --> 00:03:50,076
When it came to business,

83
00:03:50,276 --> 00:03:53,176
I really didn't want to lose.

84
00:03:53,416 --> 00:03:54,945
We just need to eliminate...

85
00:03:54,946 --> 00:03:56,546
the spring cabbage dish and tteokbokki.

86
00:03:57,856 --> 00:04:00,080
(Arirang House)

87
00:04:00,237 --> 00:04:01,237
I feel like...

88
00:04:01,767 --> 00:04:03,507
the head of a family who can't bring in money.

89
00:04:04,607 --> 00:04:07,877
This is the most discouraged I've ever seen you.

90
00:04:08,537 --> 00:04:11,047
Even this is off. It hurts me to see it.

91
00:04:11,277 --> 00:04:13,977
I've worked hard in business.

92
00:04:14,977 --> 00:04:17,647
I was in a position where I was giving advice to others.

93
00:04:18,487 --> 00:04:20,887
But it feels like I've gone back to square one.

94
00:04:22,057 --> 00:04:24,857
(He ended the lunch service in 19th place.)

95
00:04:24,887 --> 00:04:27,597
Looking back, I should've focused...

96
00:04:27,757 --> 00:04:29,597
on dishes that catch the eye.

97
00:04:29,897 --> 00:04:33,796
Food that people don't eat every day. Or something simple.

98
00:04:33,797 --> 00:04:35,837
Maybe I should've paid more attention to that.

99
00:04:35,967 --> 00:04:39,707
Was it wrong to propose a full course meal?

100
00:04:40,107 --> 00:04:42,177
I must have miscalculated.

101
00:04:42,977 --> 00:04:45,546
I needed a strategy change.

102
00:04:45,547 --> 00:04:48,647
I had to give it everything I've got.

103
00:04:49,217 --> 00:04:50,386
First of all, rice is out.

104
00:04:50,387 --> 00:04:51,617
- No rice.
- Okay.

105
00:04:52,517 --> 00:04:56,487
Why don't we serve plenty of pork for bossam?

106
00:04:57,557 --> 00:04:58,727
That could be better.

107
00:05:00,327 --> 00:05:01,927
Since our kimchi for bossam is good,

108
00:05:02,697 --> 00:05:05,167
we can make bossam and makguksu.

109
00:05:05,797 --> 00:05:07,037
We made a bold change.

110
00:05:07,197 --> 00:05:10,907
We had leftover vegetables from the spring cabbage bibimbap.

111
00:05:11,037 --> 00:05:14,536
We used them to make perilla oil makguksu.

112
00:05:14,537 --> 00:05:15,877
(Spring cabbage perilla oil makguksu)

113
00:05:16,107 --> 00:05:18,277
We found napa cabbage at the supermarket.

114
00:05:18,507 --> 00:05:21,017
We salted the cabbage and set it aside.

115
00:05:21,117 --> 00:05:24,217
We also had fresh kimchi seasoning left over from lunch service.

116
00:05:24,447 --> 00:05:27,716
We thought of making a set menu...

117
00:05:27,717 --> 00:05:31,426
with bossam, kimchi, and various sides.

118
00:05:31,427 --> 00:05:32,756
(Bossam and 3 types of kimchi)

119
00:05:32,757 --> 00:05:34,697
(Radish kimchi, white kimchi, spring cabbage kimchi)

120
00:05:34,897 --> 00:05:36,556
- Let's stay confident.
- Yes.

121
00:05:36,557 --> 00:05:37,597
Be confident.

122
00:05:39,297 --> 00:05:41,436
I thought that Sunlin would...

123
00:05:41,437 --> 00:05:42,736
crush everyone.

124
00:05:42,737 --> 00:05:45,137
I didn't expect them to come in last.

125
00:05:45,867 --> 00:05:47,036
(Sunlin)

126
00:05:47,037 --> 00:05:48,707
In the end, we finished last.

127
00:05:49,377 --> 00:05:50,977
In the end, we came last.

128
00:05:51,547 --> 00:05:53,047
In the end, we finished last.

129
00:05:55,347 --> 00:05:58,647
We didn't even make 1,000 dollars during lunch service.

130
00:06:00,817 --> 00:06:01,887
Something clearly went wrong.

131
00:06:03,157 --> 00:06:04,226
We got more orders.

132
00:06:04,227 --> 00:06:05,956
(Sunlin was very busy during lunch.)

133
00:06:05,957 --> 00:06:07,156
Fry whatever we have.

134
00:06:07,157 --> 00:06:09,257
Three if there are three. Two if there are two.

135
00:06:09,397 --> 00:06:11,427
We have to keep making jjajang.

136
00:06:12,397 --> 00:06:13,467
Did we reach 1,000 dollars yet?

137
00:06:14,767 --> 00:06:16,637
We've been insanely busy.

138
00:06:18,037 --> 00:06:19,237
We made 440 dollars so far.

139
00:06:19,367 --> 00:06:21,137
- What?
- We made 440 dollars.

140
00:06:22,537 --> 00:06:24,047
Only 440 dollars?

141
00:06:25,447 --> 00:06:26,847
My gosh. Unbelievable.

142
00:06:27,547 --> 00:06:31,347
It's because Sunlin started at negative 200 dollars.

143
00:06:31,617 --> 00:06:33,787
As I said, the costs must be under 300 dollars.

144
00:06:35,417 --> 00:06:38,056
- Sunlin, 9.5 dollars.
- That's very cheap.

145
00:06:38,057 --> 00:06:39,086
It looks delicious.

146
00:06:39,087 --> 00:06:40,096
(Negative 176.9 dollars)

147
00:06:40,097 --> 00:06:42,726
(Sunlin started the sales race at negative 170 dollars.)

148
00:06:42,727 --> 00:06:45,726
- The ingredient cost.
- Gosh, that's a lot.

149
00:06:45,727 --> 00:06:48,867
(Before deducting ingredient cost, Sunlin in 14th place)

150
00:06:48,967 --> 00:06:52,337
(After deducting ingredient cost, Sunlin in 18th place)

151
00:06:52,567 --> 00:06:55,077
I tried to use the best ingredients.

152
00:06:55,537 --> 00:06:58,147
I came here under my name...

153
00:06:58,807 --> 00:07:01,576
It's not under your name. It's a secret.

154
00:07:01,577 --> 00:07:02,617
(Laughing)

155
00:07:02,717 --> 00:07:05,587
I still wanted to use good ingredients.

156
00:07:05,787 --> 00:07:08,756
We used premium-grade beef...

157
00:07:08,757 --> 00:07:11,357
because its texture and flavour are different.

158
00:07:11,657 --> 00:07:14,397
We also made jjajangmyeon with corn flour noodles.

159
00:07:14,557 --> 00:07:15,996
We were using good ingredients.

160
00:07:15,997 --> 00:07:18,067
Our preparation was excessive.

161
00:07:18,597 --> 00:07:20,537
When we deduct the excessive cost,

162
00:07:20,837 --> 00:07:22,296
we still need to make 800 dollars.

163
00:07:22,297 --> 00:07:23,737
(Sunlin needs to sell about 730-dollar worth of food.)

164
00:07:23,937 --> 00:07:27,137
In my view, we need to change the strategy.

165
00:07:27,907 --> 00:07:30,547
We can do it. There's nothing we can't handle.

166
00:07:32,547 --> 00:07:35,147
(Smoke starts rising.)

167
00:07:35,847 --> 00:07:37,087
Are you removing the existing menu items?

168
00:07:37,217 --> 00:07:38,717
No, we'll keep them.

169
00:07:39,747 --> 00:07:41,557
He wants to add one more.

170
00:07:42,557 --> 00:07:45,087
As expected, the master adjusts instantly.

171
00:07:46,457 --> 00:07:47,526
Do you have all the ingredients?

172
00:07:47,527 --> 00:07:48,527
(Coughing)

173
00:07:48,528 --> 00:07:49,697
Yes, we do.

174
00:07:50,267 --> 00:07:51,267
That's incredible.

175
00:07:51,527 --> 00:07:53,766
(Coughing)

176
00:07:53,767 --> 00:07:55,436
It also burns for the chef who's stir-frying.

177
00:07:55,437 --> 00:07:57,437
- What?
- It also burns for the chef.

178
00:07:57,967 --> 00:07:59,637
They suddenly added nanja wanseu on the menu.

179
00:07:59,967 --> 00:08:01,907
- I see.
- I guess he can make it easily.

180
00:08:02,337 --> 00:08:03,747
Chinese chefs can adapt on the spot,

181
00:08:04,307 --> 00:08:05,807
don't you think?

182
00:08:07,177 --> 00:08:10,687
(What's the new dish that Sunlin is preparing?)

183
00:08:10,987 --> 00:08:14,086
Evening menus sell best...

184
00:08:14,087 --> 00:08:16,387
when they're rich and heavy.

185
00:08:17,227 --> 00:08:19,427
We must sell meat. Let's sell nanja wanseu.

186
00:08:20,857 --> 00:08:23,867
(Sunlin's additional menu: Nanja wanseu)

187
00:08:23,997 --> 00:08:27,266
If we do this, you have to use the wok nonstop.

188
00:08:27,267 --> 00:08:28,467
It's all right.

189
00:08:29,297 --> 00:08:32,007
Let's use scallions and whatever leftover ingredients we have.

190
00:08:32,537 --> 00:08:34,036
Let's give it a try.

191
00:08:34,037 --> 00:08:36,377
(After buying the bare minimum vegetables)

192
00:08:37,447 --> 00:08:40,177
- Minced pork and...
- And beef.

193
00:08:40,317 --> 00:08:41,377
Add some beef too.

194
00:08:41,777 --> 00:08:44,117
We knead the meat to tenderize it.

195
00:08:44,347 --> 00:08:46,047
Are you going to make it spicy?

196
00:08:46,517 --> 00:08:47,557
A little spicy?

197
00:08:47,587 --> 00:08:49,386
It's better to make it spicy for dinner.

198
00:08:49,387 --> 00:08:50,487
Let's make it spicy.

199
00:08:52,557 --> 00:08:55,057
Make the meatballs round and deep-fry them.

200
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:58,797
Coat them with spicy laojiao sauce.

201
00:09:04,367 --> 00:09:07,237
(Beef pork shrimp nanja wanseu, 25 dollars)

202
00:09:07,507 --> 00:09:09,076
(Selling a total of 4 dishes)

203
00:09:09,077 --> 00:09:10,807
(Five-colour bibim jjajang, yellow chilli meat rice bowl...)

204
00:09:11,107 --> 00:09:12,377
Are you ready? Shall we start?

205
00:09:18,317 --> 00:09:21,217
Round 1 of the 1,000-dollar sales race,

206
00:09:21,517 --> 00:09:23,086
the dinner service begins now.

207
00:09:23,087 --> 00:09:24,487
We can turn the tables.

208
00:09:24,827 --> 00:09:26,087
We can do this.

209
00:09:27,697 --> 00:09:28,897
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

210
00:09:28,997 --> 00:09:30,327
- Come on.
- Come on.

211
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:34,966
The doors to the Street Arena are opening.

212
00:09:34,967 --> 00:09:36,167
(The dinner service starts.)

213
00:09:38,907 --> 00:09:41,137
- My goodness.
- Gosh, what's all this?

214
00:09:41,477 --> 00:09:43,377
- Goodness.
- There's so much to eat.

215
00:09:44,307 --> 00:09:46,446
- This is fascinating.
- What is?

216
00:09:46,447 --> 00:09:47,617
There's something fascinating about it.

217
00:09:48,277 --> 00:09:50,787
- Where shall we sit?
- Over here.

218
00:09:52,117 --> 00:09:54,187
- They're coming. They're families.
- They're here.

219
00:09:54,757 --> 00:09:56,217
I'm a bit worried today.

220
00:09:56,987 --> 00:09:58,957
Everyone came with children.

221
00:09:59,087 --> 00:10:00,957
Our dish is also suitable for family.

222
00:10:01,457 --> 00:10:04,297
Children love jjajangmyeon.

223
00:10:05,327 --> 00:10:06,697
Shall we sit here?

224
00:10:07,167 --> 00:10:08,236
Are the customers coming in?

225
00:10:08,237 --> 00:10:09,537
(Street Arena)

226
00:10:09,897 --> 00:10:11,207
Everyone is coming.

227
00:10:12,207 --> 00:10:14,607
(1st place, Choi Sang Hyun)

228
00:10:14,807 --> 00:10:17,807
(2nd place, Lim Ki Hak)

229
00:10:18,247 --> 00:10:21,376
- Hello.
- This is how Survival Room looks.

230
00:10:21,377 --> 00:10:22,576
Congratulations.

231
00:10:22,577 --> 00:10:24,487
(3rd place, Jo Seo Hyung)

232
00:10:26,117 --> 00:10:29,757
(The survivors can watch those who haven't finished selling.)

233
00:10:29,787 --> 00:10:33,027
(Located inside the arena)

234
00:10:33,357 --> 00:10:35,297
BokBok is still receiving orders.

235
00:10:35,827 --> 00:10:36,997
BokBok and...

236
00:10:37,327 --> 00:10:40,067
Koreans are definitely uncomfortable with sitting too close.

237
00:10:41,397 --> 00:10:43,437
There are many families for dinner.

238
00:10:43,707 --> 00:10:45,867
It has to be something you can share with children.

239
00:10:46,937 --> 00:10:49,237
Seol Lin, what do you want to try? Pick one.

240
00:10:50,747 --> 00:10:53,007
What's this? It's tteokgalbi.

241
00:10:53,177 --> 00:10:54,677
What's tteokgalbi?

242
00:10:54,777 --> 00:10:56,047
Let's take a look around.

243
00:10:58,017 --> 00:10:59,817
"Futomaki Butadon."

244
00:10:59,917 --> 00:11:01,157
Pick something for Seol Lin first.

245
00:11:01,687 --> 00:11:02,887
Something for our baby?

246
00:11:03,757 --> 00:11:05,127
Lin, what do you want?

247
00:11:05,887 --> 00:11:07,457
Seol Lin, what would you like?

248
00:11:07,897 --> 00:11:09,357
I want this.

249
00:11:09,597 --> 00:11:10,697
It's too...

250
00:11:12,127 --> 00:11:13,226
For the baby...

251
00:11:13,227 --> 00:11:15,037
(Pork galbi exploding with butter, Shanghai vermicelli tteokbokki)

252
00:11:15,497 --> 00:11:16,667
Min's.

253
00:11:18,107 --> 00:11:19,237
Karaage?

254
00:11:19,667 --> 00:11:22,177
(They skip it for now.)

255
00:11:22,637 --> 00:11:24,607
Noodles? That sounds good.

256
00:11:25,447 --> 00:11:27,147
Noodles are the best for babies.

257
00:11:27,277 --> 00:11:28,317
Noodles.

258
00:11:28,547 --> 00:11:29,946
Do you want raw fish guksu?

259
00:11:29,947 --> 00:11:32,117
- She can't eat raw fish guksu.
- You can have it.

260
00:11:32,247 --> 00:11:34,486
- It's bibim guksu.
- Is it?

261
00:11:34,487 --> 00:11:36,757
(Raw fish guksu is hard to eat for the baby.)

262
00:11:37,587 --> 00:11:38,827
- Did they leave?
- They left.

263
00:11:39,757 --> 00:11:41,597
Because of their child. She can't eat raw fish guksu.

264
00:11:42,297 --> 00:11:43,426
Goodness.

265
00:11:43,427 --> 00:11:44,527
(With the family crowd becoming a key variable)

266
00:11:44,927 --> 00:11:46,627
I want to order something fast.

267
00:11:48,037 --> 00:11:49,367
Shall we order this?

268
00:11:50,237 --> 00:11:51,907
Seol Lin would eat this.

269
00:11:52,607 --> 00:11:59,007
(Which dish will the first family pick?)

270
00:11:59,377 --> 00:12:01,076
Neapolitan pizza?

271
00:12:01,077 --> 00:12:02,517
(Deep-fried pizza)

272
00:12:03,047 --> 00:12:05,387
Seol Lin would eat this. Deep-fried pizza.

273
00:12:05,487 --> 00:12:07,887
- Neapolitan deep-fried pizza?
- Deep-fried.

274
00:12:08,417 --> 00:12:09,417
Please order it.

275
00:12:10,017 --> 00:12:11,087
Please order it.

276
00:12:12,157 --> 00:12:14,057
- I'm nervous.
- Me too.

277
00:12:14,327 --> 00:12:16,197
- Do you want this?
- I told you.

278
00:12:16,497 --> 00:12:17,727
I want this.

279
00:12:17,867 --> 00:12:19,166
Do you want to order it?

280
00:12:19,167 --> 00:12:21,436
- Yes.
- Would you like to order?

281
00:12:21,437 --> 00:12:22,497
Yes.

282
00:12:25,137 --> 00:12:26,207
The order came in.

283
00:12:27,677 --> 00:12:28,677
The order came in.

284
00:12:29,077 --> 00:12:31,577
- I'll start deep-frying it.
- Okay.

285
00:12:32,577 --> 00:12:35,976
Hello, I run two Italian restaurants.

286
00:12:35,977 --> 00:12:37,347
I'm Shin Ga Young.

287
00:12:39,287 --> 00:12:42,316
My husband and I run two restaurants.

288
00:12:42,317 --> 00:12:43,827
(Lim Hong Geun, co-owner and chef)

289
00:12:43,987 --> 00:12:46,657
We focus mainly on handmade pasta.

290
00:12:47,157 --> 00:12:50,896
We try to create pasta that's not easy to find...

291
00:12:50,897 --> 00:12:51,967
anywhere else.

292
00:12:52,827 --> 00:12:56,267
For the past three years, every time reservations opened,

293
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:58,907
we were fully booked until the following month.

294
00:12:59,907 --> 00:13:03,807
In 2025, we were selected in the Michelin Guide.

295
00:13:04,877 --> 00:13:08,877
Everyone else here is incredibly accomplished.

296
00:13:09,017 --> 00:13:12,347
(At the opening ceremony)

297
00:13:12,417 --> 00:13:13,417
I can't believe it.

298
00:13:14,887 --> 00:13:16,687
I've gotten his autograph once.

299
00:13:18,057 --> 00:13:19,057
Lim Ki Hak.

300
00:13:19,058 --> 00:13:22,157
(As masters appear 1 by 1...)

301
00:13:24,197 --> 00:13:25,397
How can I beat them?

302
00:13:25,797 --> 00:13:27,567
I shouldn't have come here.

303
00:13:27,697 --> 00:13:29,667
There are so many top-tier chefs.

304
00:13:30,767 --> 00:13:33,007
Everyone except us is famous.

305
00:13:33,367 --> 00:13:35,137
They're all incredible chefs.

306
00:13:36,107 --> 00:13:39,047
I just don't want to end up being the bottom two teams.

307
00:13:39,947 --> 00:13:41,277
I'll do my best.

308
00:13:43,147 --> 00:13:44,547
This dough is done nicely.

309
00:13:45,247 --> 00:13:47,147
The signature menu of our booth...

310
00:13:47,287 --> 00:13:49,416
is Neapolitan deep-fried pizza.

311
00:13:49,417 --> 00:13:50,557
(Neapolitan deep-fried pizza)

312
00:13:51,287 --> 00:13:52,657
We'd kneaded the dough in advance...

313
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:56,197
and had it fermented in the fridge.

314
00:13:57,627 --> 00:13:59,497
I've never cooked so much at once before.

315
00:14:02,297 --> 00:14:04,066
Cut it into smaller pieces and make them into balls.

316
00:14:04,067 --> 00:14:05,637
(They shape each piece of dough.)

317
00:14:08,337 --> 00:14:10,707
(Tomato cheese sauce added)

318
00:14:10,847 --> 00:14:12,546
We should make it big.

319
00:14:12,547 --> 00:14:13,917
(Fold it into a half-moon shape.)

320
00:14:16,077 --> 00:14:19,446
(Deep-fried pizza expands like bread when deep-fried.)

321
00:14:19,447 --> 00:14:21,287
Flour tastes even better when deep-fried.

322
00:14:22,087 --> 00:14:24,157
- It's so well-cooked.
- This is insane.

323
00:14:25,427 --> 00:14:28,497
We made the pizza special by deep-frying it,

324
00:14:29,397 --> 00:14:32,097
and we served it with salad to add the crunchy texture.

325
00:14:33,367 --> 00:14:35,097
It's so nicely deep-fried.

326
00:14:42,637 --> 00:14:44,477
- It's deep-fried pizza.
- Deep-fried pizza.

327
00:14:44,577 --> 00:14:47,146
Let's eat this.

328
00:14:47,147 --> 00:14:49,417
- I really want to try this.
- You do?

329
00:14:50,017 --> 00:14:51,246
It's deep-fried pizza.

330
00:14:51,247 --> 00:14:52,917
It sounds good. I'll order one.

331
00:14:55,457 --> 00:14:56,957
The orders are coming in.

332
00:14:58,827 --> 00:15:00,127
It's a large portion.

333
00:15:02,657 --> 00:15:04,697
I hope the customers like it.

334
00:15:06,997 --> 00:15:08,467
Please give me more!

335
00:15:08,867 --> 00:15:09,867
The pizza?

336
00:15:10,037 --> 00:15:11,607
You must really like it.

337
00:15:12,607 --> 00:15:14,037
She normally doesn't ask for more.

338
00:15:24,687 --> 00:15:26,847
You really scrape the plate.

339
00:15:27,957 --> 00:15:29,017
It's to my taste.

340
00:15:29,187 --> 00:15:30,757
- Really? I'm glad to hear that.
- It's good.

341
00:15:32,727 --> 00:15:34,727
We should choose what we want first.

342
00:15:35,227 --> 00:15:36,397
There are a lot of options.

343
00:15:36,597 --> 00:15:38,097
- There are so many.
- Exactly.

344
00:15:38,427 --> 00:15:39,597
Where shall we sit?

345
00:15:40,837 --> 00:15:41,897
Tteokbokki.

346
00:15:42,937 --> 00:15:44,907
(She has a very definitive preference.)

347
00:15:46,167 --> 00:15:47,907
We need to go and order. Choose.

348
00:15:48,237 --> 00:15:49,737
- I want...
- Tteokbokki.

349
00:15:51,447 --> 00:15:53,246
(The tteokbokki girl heads to...)

350
00:15:53,247 --> 00:15:54,247
It looks good.

351
00:15:54,248 --> 00:15:55,346
(Everything About Tteokbokki)

352
00:15:55,347 --> 00:15:56,347
Okay.

353
00:15:56,348 --> 00:15:58,347
(Everything About Tteokbokki)

354
00:16:00,217 --> 00:16:03,287
Hello. I run Dookki, the global franchise.

355
00:16:03,657 --> 00:16:05,186
I'm Kim Kwan Hoon.

356
00:16:05,187 --> 00:16:06,687
(The chair of the club "Everything About Tteokbokki")

357
00:16:08,657 --> 00:16:10,967
At first, I ran a tteokbokki club.

358
00:16:12,967 --> 00:16:14,466
I ate tteokbokki from all around the country...

359
00:16:14,467 --> 00:16:16,997
and learned a lot of recipes.

360
00:16:17,507 --> 00:16:19,237
One day, I thought,

361
00:16:19,667 --> 00:16:22,277
"Tteokbokki is so delicious. Why don't I promote it overseas?"

362
00:16:22,507 --> 00:16:23,806
That's how I established the brand...

363
00:16:23,807 --> 00:16:25,447
and started promoting tteokbokki globally.

364
00:16:25,647 --> 00:16:26,807
Do you use Gemini?

365
00:16:27,007 --> 00:16:30,116
Ask Gemini, "Who is most famous for tteokbokki?"

366
00:16:30,117 --> 00:16:31,247
You'll get my name.

367
00:16:31,987 --> 00:16:33,446
(Who is most famous for tteokbokki?)

368
00:16:33,447 --> 00:16:34,656
(The most symbolic and famous person is Grandma Ma Bok Rim.)

369
00:16:34,657 --> 00:16:36,116
(1. The start of the legend: Grandma Ma Bok Rim)

370
00:16:36,117 --> 00:16:38,086
(The rising stars of tteokbokki)

371
00:16:38,087 --> 00:16:39,087
(CEO Kim Kwan Hoon)

372
00:16:39,087 --> 00:16:40,087
Not as the first person,

373
00:16:40,088 --> 00:16:43,357
but since "Doo" of Dookki sounds like "two," I'm second.

374
00:16:43,997 --> 00:16:46,427
I have about 250 shops in Korea.

375
00:16:47,567 --> 00:16:50,067
The Philippines, Taiwan, Indonesia, Thailand,

376
00:16:50,297 --> 00:16:52,307
Vietnam, Australia, the USA and so on.

377
00:16:52,467 --> 00:16:55,677
I run over 200 shops across 10 countries.

378
00:16:55,977 --> 00:16:58,677
The annual revenue is a bit less than 300 million dollars.

379
00:16:59,447 --> 00:17:00,977
I only know how to cook tteokbokki,

380
00:17:01,077 --> 00:17:02,647
I only know how to eat tteokbokki,

381
00:17:02,847 --> 00:17:04,616
and tteokbokki is the only thing I can make well.

382
00:17:04,617 --> 00:17:07,786
As a tteokbokki lover, I'll show you everything about tteokbokki.

383
00:17:07,787 --> 00:17:09,417
(I'll show you Everything About Tteokbokki.)

384
00:17:10,057 --> 00:17:12,327
The signboard says "Everything About Tteokbokki."

385
00:17:12,487 --> 00:17:15,226
So obviously, I prepared tteokbokki.

386
00:17:15,227 --> 00:17:16,526
(Tteokbokki, 5 dollars)

387
00:17:16,527 --> 00:17:17,766
(Flour rice cake, rice rice cake)

388
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:19,497
And I prepared Busan fishcakes.

389
00:17:20,197 --> 00:17:22,996
I made snowflake-shaped fritters so they look pretty.

390
00:17:22,997 --> 00:17:24,367
They're homemade.

391
00:17:25,207 --> 00:17:27,206
(Tteokbokki's best friend)

392
00:17:27,207 --> 00:17:29,477
(Fritters)

393
00:17:33,277 --> 00:17:35,217
He kept deep-frying fritters.

394
00:17:35,847 --> 00:17:38,987
(He stood firmly at his position.)

395
00:17:39,417 --> 00:17:42,256
He's been deep-frying fritters for five hours straight.

396
00:17:42,257 --> 00:17:43,557
- Who?
- Him.

397
00:17:50,697 --> 00:17:53,497
CEO Shin can deep-fry everything, down to your shoes.

398
00:17:54,537 --> 00:17:56,937
I've studied fritters for 30 years.

399
00:17:57,507 --> 00:17:59,106
I'm Shin Jong Hun, the master of fritters.

400
00:17:59,107 --> 00:18:00,567
(The owner of Shin Jong Hun Tendon Master)

401
00:18:00,807 --> 00:18:03,037
He knows everything about tteokbokki.

402
00:18:03,507 --> 00:18:05,076
I know everything about fritters.

403
00:18:05,077 --> 00:18:06,246
(Everything About Fritters)

404
00:18:06,247 --> 00:18:08,646
I use my techniques...

405
00:18:08,647 --> 00:18:11,017
to make the fritters look fancy.

406
00:18:11,647 --> 00:18:13,817
I added the flakes front and back...

407
00:18:14,017 --> 00:18:16,317
while keeping it crispy.

408
00:18:17,217 --> 00:18:19,087
Nothing beats fritters.

409
00:18:20,457 --> 00:18:21,897
You deep-fried pineapples?

410
00:18:22,527 --> 00:18:24,897
It's fritter plus dessert.

411
00:18:25,027 --> 00:18:26,566
It's refreshing.

412
00:18:26,567 --> 00:18:28,567
- Isn't gimmari pretty too?
- That's gimmari?

413
00:18:29,667 --> 00:18:32,107
I think I was the first to invent it.

414
00:18:32,707 --> 00:18:36,107
(A fritter designer)

415
00:18:36,577 --> 00:18:39,177
I wanted it to stand out.

416
00:18:40,977 --> 00:18:43,847
(Deep-fried gimmari)

417
00:18:45,217 --> 00:18:47,986
(Tteokmo set, 12.90 dollars)

418
00:18:47,987 --> 00:18:49,257
Tteokbokki...

419
00:18:49,417 --> 00:18:52,757
can't replace a meal. I'm clearly aware of it.

420
00:18:52,857 --> 00:18:56,356
This commercial district and that time of the day mean...

421
00:18:56,357 --> 00:18:57,727
people come for a full meal.

422
00:18:57,867 --> 00:19:00,266
- So...
- We shouldn't try to become...

423
00:19:00,267 --> 00:19:02,337
the main dish or to serve them with a full meal.

424
00:19:02,797 --> 00:19:05,737
When others serve their food as the main dish,

425
00:19:06,037 --> 00:19:07,837
let's become each table's side dish.

426
00:19:08,007 --> 00:19:09,877
Let's become the perfect supporting role.

427
00:19:10,007 --> 00:19:12,877
Becoming the perfect extra was my strategy.

428
00:19:13,047 --> 00:19:16,717
"Instead, every single table will have our dish."

429
00:19:16,847 --> 00:19:19,416
Set the price at 10 dollars-ish and aim for 100 customers.

430
00:19:19,417 --> 00:19:21,856
Then we'd be done in an hour.

431
00:19:21,857 --> 00:19:23,256
(A great menu to share plus low unit cost equals 1 hour?)

432
00:19:23,257 --> 00:19:25,926
We'll show you what a tteokbokki maniac...

433
00:19:25,927 --> 00:19:28,296
and a fritter maniac can do.

434
00:19:28,297 --> 00:19:29,857
- Let's do this.
- Let's do this.

435
00:19:30,357 --> 00:19:31,496
I don't know about the ranking,

436
00:19:31,497 --> 00:19:32,827
but we won't be open for dinner.

437
00:19:34,537 --> 00:19:35,567
Yes.

438
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:39,567
The dinner business of Round One starts.

439
00:19:45,177 --> 00:19:46,177
Well...

440
00:19:47,007 --> 00:19:48,717
We thought we'd be done by lunch,

441
00:19:49,347 --> 00:19:51,887
but we couldn't.

442
00:19:52,647 --> 00:19:55,556
Tteokbokki is so basic.

443
00:19:55,557 --> 00:19:56,886
I think that's why it doesn't have many customers.

444
00:19:56,887 --> 00:19:58,057
- It doesn't?
- No.

445
00:19:58,627 --> 00:19:59,987
Tteokbokki looks so good.

446
00:20:00,787 --> 00:20:02,097
But it's just tteokbokki.

447
00:20:02,627 --> 00:20:05,067
Is tteokbokki too plain?

448
00:20:05,297 --> 00:20:06,367
Exactly.

449
00:20:07,267 --> 00:20:09,766
No matter how good tteokbokki is, it's still tteokbokki.

450
00:20:09,767 --> 00:20:10,767
I agree.

451
00:20:11,137 --> 00:20:14,937
"I won't eat something I can easily find around me."

452
00:20:15,377 --> 00:20:18,207
Eating something new once in a while...

453
00:20:18,507 --> 00:20:20,976
can bring the customers joy.

454
00:20:20,977 --> 00:20:22,347
I completely felt that.

455
00:20:22,977 --> 00:20:25,316
We need a menu which children can eat.

456
00:20:25,317 --> 00:20:27,187
Tteokbokki would work, then.

457
00:20:28,287 --> 00:20:30,817
We have better chance if children come.

458
00:20:31,157 --> 00:20:32,187
Right.

459
00:20:32,287 --> 00:20:33,327
This?

460
00:20:33,427 --> 00:20:34,797
You order from here.

461
00:20:35,357 --> 00:20:37,156
Add the menu here, pay here,

462
00:20:37,157 --> 00:20:38,627
and let's go buy something else.

463
00:20:39,397 --> 00:20:40,596
You must finish what you ordered.

464
00:20:40,597 --> 00:20:41,836
(The family orders tteokbokki as a side dish.)

465
00:20:41,837 --> 00:20:43,737
- Add string cheese and...
- My gosh.

466
00:20:43,937 --> 00:20:45,207
- Here it is.
- Let's go.

467
00:20:53,077 --> 00:20:56,577
(Served in 1 minute)

468
00:21:02,257 --> 00:21:03,717
Be careful when you carry it.

469
00:21:04,287 --> 00:21:05,327
It's hot.

470
00:21:07,627 --> 00:21:09,357
(Surprised)

471
00:21:09,727 --> 00:21:11,627
It does taste different.

472
00:21:12,167 --> 00:21:14,127
- It's different, right?
- It's different.

473
00:21:15,167 --> 00:21:17,066
I took a sip of the fishcake soup...

474
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:18,637
and had tteokbokki. It tastes good like that.

475
00:21:18,767 --> 00:21:20,737
The fishcake soup is delicious.

476
00:21:21,677 --> 00:21:22,877
Mom.

477
00:21:23,577 --> 00:21:25,477
Almost everyone is eating...

478
00:21:25,647 --> 00:21:28,017
Everything About Tteokbokki.

479
00:21:28,517 --> 00:21:29,877
- Everything About Tteokbokki?
- Yes.

480
00:21:30,217 --> 00:21:31,947
They're eating it too.

481
00:21:32,847 --> 00:21:34,557
It's soft and chewy.

482
00:21:34,717 --> 00:21:35,856
They ordered fritters.

483
00:21:35,857 --> 00:21:36,956
(Tteokmo set, tteokbokki, fritters set, fishcake)

484
00:21:36,957 --> 00:21:38,056
It looks good.

485
00:21:38,057 --> 00:21:41,127
(Fritters plus fishcake, tteokmo set)

486
00:21:42,057 --> 00:21:43,257
Please get colder.

487
00:21:43,827 --> 00:21:45,666
(Current Revenue: 442.90 dollars)

488
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:47,967
This was how I imagined things would go.

489
00:21:49,437 --> 00:21:51,336
- How many?
- One.

490
00:21:51,337 --> 00:21:52,367
One.

491
00:21:52,667 --> 00:21:54,737
(Plating the futomaki as soon as they receive the order)

492
00:21:55,477 --> 00:21:57,176
This pork is really tasty.

493
00:21:57,177 --> 00:21:58,306
(He stir-fries the pork while adding the smokey flavour.)

494
00:21:58,307 --> 00:22:00,976
(Poached egg)

495
00:22:00,977 --> 00:22:02,716
(A pork rice bowl with various toppings is ready.)

496
00:22:02,717 --> 00:22:03,977
(Pickled chilli, deep-fried pork skin)

497
00:22:04,247 --> 00:22:06,346
(The dinner set menu of Hohyunghojae)

498
00:22:06,347 --> 00:22:07,616
We'll make it cost-effective.

499
00:22:07,617 --> 00:22:09,016
Three maki, pork bowl,

500
00:22:09,017 --> 00:22:11,956
and fritters. That's a big portion.

501
00:22:11,957 --> 00:22:13,326
(Miso soup, karaage, 3 pieces of futomaki, pork rice bowl added)

502
00:22:13,327 --> 00:22:15,827
Brothers futomaki dinner set.

503
00:22:15,927 --> 00:22:16,996
Done.

504
00:22:16,997 --> 00:22:18,167
Why is there so much?

505
00:22:18,867 --> 00:22:19,867
We can eat them all.

506
00:22:19,867 --> 00:22:20,867
We must have it.

507
00:22:20,868 --> 00:22:22,097
- Even if we can't finish it.
- Let's go.

508
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:23,637
That's a big portion.

509
00:22:24,467 --> 00:22:25,567
It looks good.

510
00:22:26,607 --> 00:22:28,207
Ho Young, you need to speed up.

511
00:22:31,047 --> 00:22:33,077
The fourth restaurant to survive...

512
00:22:33,547 --> 00:22:35,517
the 1,000-dollar sales race is...

513
00:22:36,217 --> 00:22:37,576
Hohyunghojae.

514
00:22:37,577 --> 00:22:41,487
(Hohyunghojae finishes in 4th place.)

515
00:22:41,817 --> 00:22:42,857
- See that?
- Goodness.

516
00:22:43,357 --> 00:22:44,587
- Nice.
- We just need to finish this.

517
00:22:46,357 --> 00:22:47,797
We're done.

518
00:22:47,827 --> 00:22:48,896
Don't let your guard down...

519
00:22:48,897 --> 00:22:50,327
- Let's do our best until the end.
- until it's over.

520
00:22:54,327 --> 00:22:56,036
(4th place: Hohyunghojae by Jung Ho Young)

521
00:22:56,037 --> 00:22:57,697
(Survived in 157 minutes)

522
00:22:58,367 --> 00:22:59,436
Song Hoon.

523
00:22:59,437 --> 00:23:01,506
(Hohyunghojae)

524
00:23:01,507 --> 00:23:03,006
I gave up my face for this today.

525
00:23:03,007 --> 00:23:04,547
I'll give you one when the camera is rolling.

526
00:23:05,107 --> 00:23:06,976
- Good job.
- Thank you, Ho Young.

527
00:23:06,977 --> 00:23:08,717
- I'll drink this.
- Thanks for the drink.

528
00:23:10,277 --> 00:23:11,447
(Surprised)

529
00:23:11,587 --> 00:23:14,047
- What is it?
- It's sold out.

530
00:23:15,557 --> 00:23:16,557
(Survives)

531
00:23:16,558 --> 00:23:19,486
- No.
- No. No way.

532
00:23:19,487 --> 00:23:20,487
(Survives)

533
00:23:22,257 --> 00:23:24,257
We sold a lot, nearly 1,000 dollars. right?

534
00:23:26,067 --> 00:23:28,237
HunGry keeps getting customers, bit by bit.

535
00:23:29,067 --> 00:23:30,097
One more rice.

536
00:23:30,167 --> 00:23:31,366
Two in total, right?

537
00:23:31,367 --> 00:23:32,707
One more steak rice.

538
00:23:32,967 --> 00:23:33,967
Just stir-fry a lot at once.

539
00:23:34,167 --> 00:23:35,407
I could seriously cook 100 servings.

540
00:23:38,077 --> 00:23:39,847
There are a lot of people lining up. Keep stir-frying, okay?

541
00:23:41,007 --> 00:23:42,516
I think our menus...

542
00:23:42,517 --> 00:23:43,976
are pretty good for dinner too.

543
00:23:43,977 --> 00:23:45,747
Very. They're very good.

544
00:23:46,247 --> 00:23:47,956
Since they do a lot of big businesses,

545
00:23:47,957 --> 00:23:49,657
- they must have a lot of data.
- Exactly.

546
00:23:50,717 --> 00:23:52,527
- Where's the steak rice?
- Here.

547
00:23:53,627 --> 00:23:55,897
Dad, many people are queuing up for the steak rice.

548
00:23:56,697 --> 00:23:59,367
(In the evening, it's crowded with both children and adults.)

549
00:23:59,627 --> 00:24:00,767
They're selling well.

550
00:24:00,997 --> 00:24:03,337
A lot of people line up in front of HunGry.

551
00:24:03,697 --> 00:24:05,037
Can you just finish this?

552
00:24:05,467 --> 00:24:07,337
I'll do it.

553
00:24:08,537 --> 00:24:09,577
Lucky them.

554
00:24:10,237 --> 00:24:12,606
- I'm so envious.
- The fifth restaurant to survive...

555
00:24:12,607 --> 00:24:14,747
the 1,000-dollar sales race is...

556
00:24:16,417 --> 00:24:17,576
HunGry.

557
00:24:17,577 --> 00:24:18,646
(HunGry finishes in 5th place.)

558
00:24:18,647 --> 00:24:20,987
- Serve them first.
- We need to finish serving.

559
00:24:22,687 --> 00:24:24,256
- Are you closed?
- Sorry?

560
00:24:24,257 --> 00:24:26,126
- Are you closed?
- Yes, we're done today.

561
00:24:26,127 --> 00:24:27,357
- Sorry.
- They're closed.

562
00:24:28,327 --> 00:24:30,127
- Fifth place!
- Fifth place!

563
00:24:30,497 --> 00:24:32,766
I'm so happy now. I love it.

564
00:24:32,767 --> 00:24:33,797
(5th place: HunGry by Kim Hoon, Survived in 162 minutes)

565
00:24:33,927 --> 00:24:36,297
The 6th restaurant to survive the 1,000-dollar sales race...

566
00:24:36,797 --> 00:24:37,937
is Gotgan.

567
00:24:38,607 --> 00:24:40,607
(Gotgan)

568
00:24:40,807 --> 00:24:41,976
(Gotgan finishes in 6th place.)

569
00:24:41,977 --> 00:24:43,077
Nice.

570
00:24:45,347 --> 00:24:48,777
(6th place: Gotgan by Kim Mi Ryeong, Survived in 166 minutes)

571
00:24:49,147 --> 00:24:50,247
It's okay.

572
00:24:50,347 --> 00:24:51,847
Don't get scared.

573
00:24:52,417 --> 00:24:55,616
(Agungi)

574
00:24:55,617 --> 00:24:56,717
Welcome!

575
00:25:00,187 --> 00:25:01,396
(Walking past)

576
00:25:01,397 --> 00:25:02,627
Let's go!

577
00:25:03,527 --> 00:25:04,997
I hear babies.

578
00:25:05,127 --> 00:25:07,297
They'll come to us when the smell the pork.

579
00:25:07,367 --> 00:25:09,267
I've experienced it many times. They'll definitely come.

580
00:25:10,537 --> 00:25:11,737
Agungi.

581
00:25:12,467 --> 00:25:14,976
- Agungi.
- Shall we try...

582
00:25:14,977 --> 00:25:16,037
this one?

583
00:25:17,477 --> 00:25:18,607
Pork.

584
00:25:20,307 --> 00:25:21,547
Let's make one round first.

585
00:25:21,977 --> 00:25:24,017
- It's pork.
- Pork.

586
00:25:24,517 --> 00:25:26,246
- Meat...
- It's butter pork.

587
00:25:26,247 --> 00:25:27,247
What sound is that?

588
00:25:27,387 --> 00:25:28,617
It's from the inside.

589
00:25:29,987 --> 00:25:31,017
Pork?

590
00:25:31,887 --> 00:25:34,597
(Another family of 3 stops in front of Agungi.)

591
00:25:34,827 --> 00:25:36,097
(Glancing)

592
00:25:36,357 --> 00:25:37,927
I think they'll place an order.

593
00:25:38,297 --> 00:25:39,967
Family units should eat pork.

594
00:25:41,367 --> 00:25:42,736
- The set...
- Or just order that.

595
00:25:42,737 --> 00:25:43,937
Shall we eat pork?

596
00:25:45,607 --> 00:25:48,977
(Will Agungi finally get their first order?)

597
00:25:49,407 --> 00:25:50,806
(Buzz)

598
00:25:50,807 --> 00:25:52,076
Nice. How many?

599
00:25:52,077 --> 00:25:53,476
Two servings of butter pork galbi.

600
00:25:53,477 --> 00:25:55,147
- Okay.
- No, just one.

601
00:25:55,347 --> 00:25:56,977
- Only the pork?
- Yes.

602
00:25:58,117 --> 00:26:02,087
(Grilling the pre-grilled pork)

603
00:26:02,457 --> 00:26:04,057
Let's go. We can do this.

604
00:26:04,787 --> 00:26:06,257
Good, the smell is spreading.

605
00:26:07,957 --> 00:26:11,667
Once the business starts, the smell and smoke will spread.

606
00:26:12,667 --> 00:26:14,596
I was desperate for them to eat my food.

607
00:26:14,597 --> 00:26:17,397
That was why I spoke loudly for them to hear.

608
00:26:17,697 --> 00:26:18,967
Hello.

609
00:26:19,007 --> 00:26:20,666
Butter pork galbi.

610
00:26:20,667 --> 00:26:22,777
Butter pork galbi is almost sold out.

611
00:26:23,807 --> 00:26:25,676
- Pork galbi.
- Hello.

612
00:26:25,677 --> 00:26:26,847
Hello.

613
00:26:27,607 --> 00:26:29,977
We get a 5-dollar discount if we eat them together.

614
00:26:30,047 --> 00:26:32,147
Shall we get one? You like that.

615
00:26:32,917 --> 00:26:34,546
(Butter pork galbi and Shanghai vermicelli tteokbokki set)

616
00:26:34,547 --> 00:26:35,617
(26 dollars)

617
00:26:35,717 --> 00:26:38,227
- One set.
- Okay, one set.

618
00:26:38,487 --> 00:26:39,857
Butter pork galbi.

619
00:26:42,457 --> 00:26:43,727
Pork galbi, let's go.

620
00:26:45,097 --> 00:26:47,067
(Deep-fried fishcake)

621
00:26:48,097 --> 00:26:50,767
(A piece of butter)

622
00:26:54,267 --> 00:26:55,576
I'll serve Shanghai tteokbokki in a big portion too.

623
00:26:55,577 --> 00:26:56,837
Okay, thanks.

624
00:26:57,837 --> 00:27:00,947
- One more pork galbi.
- Okay. Butter pork galbi.

625
00:27:01,177 --> 00:27:02,247
Let's go.

626
00:27:03,877 --> 00:27:05,147
- It has a 5-dollar discount.
- Yes.

627
00:27:05,517 --> 00:27:06,746
(Butter pork galbi and Shanghai vermicelli tteokbokki set)

628
00:27:06,747 --> 00:27:07,816
(26 dollars)

629
00:27:07,817 --> 00:27:08,857
Pork galbi.

630
00:27:09,017 --> 00:27:12,027
(Butter pork galbi, 19 dollars)

631
00:27:12,157 --> 00:27:14,827
- One more pork galbi.
- Okay. Four in total.

632
00:27:15,457 --> 00:27:16,957
The word is spreading.

633
00:27:17,497 --> 00:27:18,767
How nice.

634
00:27:19,667 --> 00:27:22,566
(The first queue to form in front of Agungi)

635
00:27:22,567 --> 00:27:23,996
It's all about the spirit.

636
00:27:23,997 --> 00:27:27,367
"We're alive." You need to shout.

637
00:27:27,607 --> 00:27:30,707
"We must survive." It was a way to express that too.

638
00:27:31,807 --> 00:27:33,306
Keep the butter pork galbi coming.

639
00:27:33,307 --> 00:27:34,677
Okay, got it.

640
00:27:34,847 --> 00:27:36,547
It's delicious.

641
00:27:37,077 --> 00:27:38,387
Pork galbi.

642
00:27:38,547 --> 00:27:40,117
It... Spring cabbage?

643
00:27:41,657 --> 00:27:44,787
Spring cabbage, bossam, and three types of kimchi.

644
00:27:45,257 --> 00:27:46,257
Really?

645
00:27:46,258 --> 00:27:47,627
Do you want bossam or this?

646
00:27:48,627 --> 00:27:49,727
- I...
- Shall we eat bossam?

647
00:27:52,597 --> 00:27:54,466
- Let's eat this.
- This?

648
00:27:54,467 --> 00:27:56,396
- This looks best.
- Okay, let's eat this.

649
00:27:56,397 --> 00:27:58,437
It looks delicious. There's pork suyuk too.

650
00:27:59,167 --> 00:28:01,206
Shall we have bossam and three types of kimchi?

651
00:28:01,207 --> 00:28:02,707
Let's order bossam medium, then.

652
00:28:04,577 --> 00:28:06,677
(Order)

653
00:28:08,747 --> 00:28:11,317
- One bossam medium.
- Okay.

654
00:28:13,147 --> 00:28:16,987
(Slice the boiled bossam nicely.)

655
00:28:19,027 --> 00:28:21,127
(White kimchi)

656
00:28:21,187 --> 00:28:22,397
(Radish kimchi)

657
00:28:25,527 --> 00:28:27,497
(Spring cabbage kimchi)

658
00:28:28,237 --> 00:28:32,167
I got more determined and angry.

659
00:28:32,737 --> 00:28:35,777
I'd be happy to place 18th.

660
00:28:36,637 --> 00:28:38,547
- I wish we'll move up 1 rank.
- Just 1.

661
00:28:38,647 --> 00:28:40,947
- Just 1 rank.
- If we move up 1 rank,

662
00:28:41,077 --> 00:28:43,716
I'll be able to go home...

663
00:28:43,717 --> 00:28:45,246
and have a deep sleep.

664
00:28:45,247 --> 00:28:46,447
Spring cabbage bossam.

665
00:28:46,717 --> 00:28:48,047
Let's eat spring cabbage.

666
00:28:48,957 --> 00:28:51,727
- It looks good.
- This is called mianbao xia.

667
00:28:52,987 --> 00:28:54,157
- My gosh.
- Is it good?

668
00:28:55,627 --> 00:28:56,697
My gosh.

669
00:28:57,127 --> 00:28:58,397
How does spring cabbage taste?

670
00:28:58,727 --> 00:28:59,866
It's similar to cabbage.

671
00:28:59,867 --> 00:29:02,337
It's a bit sweet and spicy.

672
00:29:04,837 --> 00:29:06,967
- The meat is soft.
- I want to eat this.

673
00:29:07,407 --> 00:29:09,577
Have it with the meat. The meat is soft.

674
00:29:11,947 --> 00:29:13,247
- Here.
- Bossam.

675
00:29:14,817 --> 00:29:15,817
It's heavy.

676
00:29:16,477 --> 00:29:17,477
Let's look around.

677
00:29:19,217 --> 00:29:20,586
(Arirang House)

678
00:29:20,587 --> 00:29:21,687
Bossam.

679
00:29:22,417 --> 00:29:24,857
It's a lot. I don't think I can finish it.

680
00:29:26,027 --> 00:29:27,556
It had cockles.

681
00:29:27,557 --> 00:29:31,127
(The customers just walk past.)

682
00:29:32,967 --> 00:29:35,596
(The price makes them hesitant to choose, )

683
00:29:35,597 --> 00:29:38,937
(and it has a big portion.)

684
00:29:39,107 --> 00:29:42,037
(Arirang House's orders have dried up.)

685
00:29:45,607 --> 00:29:47,177
This is bad.

686
00:29:49,717 --> 00:29:53,347
I've felt this feeling in my life a few times.

687
00:29:54,417 --> 00:29:56,856
When there are no customers in the restaurant,

688
00:29:56,857 --> 00:29:59,527
you feel the pressure in it.

689
00:30:00,727 --> 00:30:03,927
I felt that pressure...

690
00:30:04,057 --> 00:30:05,627
in this food stall too.

691
00:30:05,867 --> 00:30:07,126
My stall has no customers,

692
00:30:07,127 --> 00:30:09,837
but the neighbouring stall has orders coming in.

693
00:30:10,367 --> 00:30:13,237
I felt very dejected.

694
00:30:13,867 --> 00:30:15,377
Butter pork galbi.

695
00:30:16,507 --> 00:30:18,907
- One set.
- One set, let's go.

696
00:30:19,107 --> 00:30:21,007
(Pork galbi)

697
00:30:21,917 --> 00:30:23,347
What riled me up was,

698
00:30:24,647 --> 00:30:26,846
the owner of Agungi...

699
00:30:26,847 --> 00:30:28,387
When his sales increased,

700
00:30:28,757 --> 00:30:30,656
he started to sing...

701
00:30:30,657 --> 00:30:32,687
and hum while working.

702
00:30:33,927 --> 00:30:35,527
It felt like he was teasing me.

703
00:30:36,427 --> 00:30:37,597
How much is the pork galbi?

704
00:30:37,897 --> 00:30:39,767
- It's 19 dollars.
- It's 19 dollars.

705
00:30:40,167 --> 00:30:41,767
We must be getting on his nerves.

706
00:30:42,167 --> 00:30:43,737
Dance machine.

707
00:30:46,507 --> 00:30:48,066
I'm dancing to avoid the smoke.

708
00:30:48,067 --> 00:30:49,107
(Dancing)

709
00:30:49,737 --> 00:30:51,777
(It's very clear that he's trying to tease them.)

710
00:30:51,977 --> 00:30:54,677
- One more pork galbi.
- Okay. Four in total.

711
00:30:55,477 --> 00:30:57,117
Should I have chosen pork galbi too?

712
00:30:57,517 --> 00:31:00,017
I'm a pork galbi expert. I'm good at it.

713
00:31:01,047 --> 00:31:02,087
I...

714
00:31:03,417 --> 00:31:04,616
What should we do?

715
00:31:04,617 --> 00:31:05,856
(Arirang House)

716
00:31:05,857 --> 00:31:07,187
It feels like we're the only ones without customers.

717
00:31:07,887 --> 00:31:10,696
(Agungi)

718
00:31:10,697 --> 00:31:13,197
Agungi has 1,000 dollars left...

719
00:31:14,067 --> 00:31:15,767
to their survival.

720
00:31:15,937 --> 00:31:17,997
Darn it, we're in trouble.

721
00:31:18,667 --> 00:31:21,677
(They finally break even.)

722
00:31:21,837 --> 00:31:23,377
Good luck, Agungi!

723
00:31:24,577 --> 00:31:26,877
They're starting from scratch.

724
00:31:27,577 --> 00:31:29,747
We started in the red anyway.

725
00:31:29,917 --> 00:31:32,647
I thought, "Don't mind it."

726
00:31:33,117 --> 00:31:34,646
(Rushing)

727
00:31:34,647 --> 00:31:36,057
It's okay. Take it slow.

728
00:31:37,457 --> 00:31:38,787
Only a few more to go.

729
00:31:39,087 --> 00:31:40,756
- We have a lot more to go.
- Okay.

730
00:31:40,757 --> 00:31:41,927
(Facing reality)

731
00:31:41,997 --> 00:31:43,197
Don't get worked up, Seok Hyun.

732
00:31:45,267 --> 00:31:46,666
Doing business isn't easy.

733
00:31:46,667 --> 00:31:50,267
(Current Revenue: 0 dollars, Current Revenue: 368.32 dollars)

734
00:31:53,537 --> 00:31:55,107
BokBok always has a queue.

735
00:31:56,237 --> 00:31:58,406
Okay. Jjamppong is ready.

736
00:31:58,407 --> 00:31:59,407
Okay.

737
00:31:59,477 --> 00:32:01,147
Five, four, five, two.

738
00:32:01,207 --> 00:32:02,517
How many more?

739
00:32:03,977 --> 00:32:05,887
Why is it so hard to sell 1,000 dollars worth?

740
00:32:07,047 --> 00:32:09,487
Honestly, I'm quite shocked.

741
00:32:09,817 --> 00:32:11,187
We were planning...

742
00:32:11,317 --> 00:32:13,857
to finish the business by lunch and watch others sell their food.

743
00:32:14,157 --> 00:32:15,597
That was what we wanted, but...

744
00:32:16,827 --> 00:32:19,997
(Before the dinner business, they revealed the revenue ranking.)

745
00:32:20,967 --> 00:32:23,067
(9th place, BokBok)

746
00:32:26,967 --> 00:32:30,777
It hurt my pride.

747
00:32:31,277 --> 00:32:34,206
We must sell them quickly.

748
00:32:34,207 --> 00:32:36,346
I thought we must make it to the rank quickly...

749
00:32:36,347 --> 00:32:38,347
and escape from there.

750
00:32:38,917 --> 00:32:40,417
You wanted jjamppong.

751
00:32:41,117 --> 00:32:42,357
One jjamppong.

752
00:32:46,587 --> 00:32:47,987
We're selling more jjamppong for dinner.

753
00:32:57,267 --> 00:32:58,937
Please check the number.

754
00:33:03,837 --> 00:33:07,877
The 7th restaurant to survive the 1,000-dollar sales race is...

755
00:33:08,077 --> 00:33:09,217
What? The seventh?

756
00:33:09,777 --> 00:33:11,477
BokBok would be done soon, no?

757
00:33:12,817 --> 00:33:14,447
Don't Tell Grandma.

758
00:33:15,057 --> 00:33:16,586
(Happy)

759
00:33:16,587 --> 00:33:17,657
Really?

760
00:33:18,627 --> 00:33:20,586
(7th place: Don't Tell Grandma by Shin Ga Young)

761
00:33:20,587 --> 00:33:21,627
(Survived in 168 minutes)

762
00:33:22,327 --> 00:33:24,127
Didn't we make 1,000 dollars by now?

763
00:33:24,897 --> 00:33:26,497
We don't have enough ingredients.

764
00:33:30,937 --> 00:33:35,177
The 8th restaurant to survive the 1,000-dollar sales race is...

765
00:33:36,207 --> 00:33:37,337
BokBok.

766
00:33:38,137 --> 00:33:39,977
We're done after serving this order.

767
00:33:43,017 --> 00:33:45,216
Mianbao xia and jjamppong are ready!

768
00:33:45,217 --> 00:33:47,217
(8th place: BokBok by Lee Yeon Bok, Survived in 172 minutes)

769
00:33:47,587 --> 00:33:48,757
BokBok.

770
00:33:53,687 --> 00:33:56,697
Was it Lee Yeon Bok's... Was it BokBok this time?

771
00:33:58,297 --> 00:34:01,627
(The Chinese restaurant across the street is faltering.)

772
00:34:01,897 --> 00:34:03,736
Did we only make 500 dollars?

773
00:34:03,737 --> 00:34:05,437
- We sold 600 dollars.
- I see.

774
00:34:06,107 --> 00:34:08,136
- So another 500 dollars.
- We've got to subtract 170 dollars.

775
00:34:08,137 --> 00:34:09,177
Right.

776
00:34:10,307 --> 00:34:11,537
Compare too much,

777
00:34:11,777 --> 00:34:14,177
and we'd get frustrated and worn out.

778
00:34:14,447 --> 00:34:16,677
- Serve the dishes faster...
- Yes.

779
00:34:16,747 --> 00:34:18,317
and concentrate on our job.

780
00:34:18,787 --> 00:34:20,887
Don't let it bother us.

781
00:34:22,817 --> 00:34:23,817
Okay.

782
00:34:25,527 --> 00:34:27,826
This is bad. Everyone is walking to the other side.

783
00:34:27,827 --> 00:34:30,127
(Despite their resolve, they're drawn to the window.)

784
00:34:32,097 --> 00:34:34,726
Since BokBok closed early,

785
00:34:34,727 --> 00:34:37,867
wouldn't people line up for Sunlin?

786
00:34:38,137 --> 00:34:40,366
(Sunlin)

787
00:34:40,367 --> 00:34:41,637
This place sells Chinese dishes.

788
00:34:43,677 --> 00:34:45,507
I bet they're done with business.

789
00:34:48,307 --> 00:34:49,516
Actually, we can still order.

790
00:34:49,517 --> 00:34:50,647
- Can we?
- Yes.

791
00:34:50,847 --> 00:34:52,187
Did you see that?

792
00:34:52,847 --> 00:34:54,286
- Should we try something new?
- I'm in.

793
00:34:54,287 --> 00:34:55,617
- I want jjajangmyeon.
- Okay.

794
00:34:55,887 --> 00:34:57,157
So this is the menu.

795
00:34:58,187 --> 00:34:59,257
What should we get?

796
00:34:59,687 --> 00:35:01,326
How about the new version of mianbao xia?

797
00:35:01,327 --> 00:35:02,797
Or the five-colour bibim jjajang?

798
00:35:02,897 --> 00:35:06,127
Five-colour bibim jjajang meal.

799
00:35:06,967 --> 00:35:08,797
Do the noodles, Dad. I'll make the youtiao xia.

800
00:35:08,837 --> 00:35:09,867
Okay.

801
00:35:12,337 --> 00:35:15,907
Dinner business went more smoothly than lunch business.

802
00:35:17,207 --> 00:35:20,977
The 9th restaurant to survive the 1,000-dollar sales race is...

803
00:35:21,877 --> 00:35:23,017
Number One.

804
00:35:24,347 --> 00:35:26,287
- Gosh, Number One.
- What?

805
00:35:27,117 --> 00:35:28,187
Number One.

806
00:35:28,587 --> 00:35:31,617
Thank you.

807
00:35:33,487 --> 00:35:35,627
Ji Beom, we did it.

808
00:35:36,497 --> 00:35:38,927
I almost cried, thinking we'd get eliminated.

809
00:35:41,067 --> 00:35:44,837
The 10th restaurant to survive the 1,000-dollar sales race is...

810
00:35:46,107 --> 00:35:47,137
Goal!

811
00:35:51,437 --> 00:35:52,777
(Number One)

812
00:35:53,877 --> 00:35:55,317
Congratulations!

813
00:35:58,047 --> 00:35:59,047
Goal!

814
00:36:00,047 --> 00:36:01,117
Goal!

815
00:36:02,317 --> 00:36:05,326
- Thank you.
- Well done, Min Hyuk.

816
00:36:05,327 --> 00:36:06,327
(9th place: Number One by Kwak Dong Hoon, )

817
00:36:06,327 --> 00:36:07,327
(10th place: Goal! by Hong Seok Cheon, )

818
00:36:10,957 --> 00:36:12,027
It's tteokgalbi.

819
00:36:12,997 --> 00:36:14,797
Is it popcorn?

820
00:36:15,197 --> 00:36:16,937
Why is there popcorn here?

821
00:36:18,137 --> 00:36:19,236
Gosh, look over there.

822
00:36:19,237 --> 00:36:21,337
- Place the order?
- Hi.

823
00:36:23,437 --> 00:36:24,477
Here it comes.

824
00:36:27,147 --> 00:36:29,576
(Streaming live outside)

825
00:36:29,577 --> 00:36:33,047
(Now streaming live)

826
00:36:33,647 --> 00:36:34,686
All set.

827
00:36:34,687 --> 00:36:37,117
(Ordered through the live stream)

828
00:36:38,727 --> 00:36:40,657
- Here's our first order.
- Here it is.

829
00:36:42,097 --> 00:36:43,197
The first order.

830
00:36:43,627 --> 00:36:46,896
I'm Chef Kim Hee Eun, currently running the restaurants...

831
00:36:46,897 --> 00:36:48,167
SOUL and Egg and Flour.

832
00:36:48,767 --> 00:36:51,837
The restaurants are in Haebangchon, Yongsan.

833
00:36:51,967 --> 00:36:55,336
We earned a Michelin One Star...

834
00:36:55,337 --> 00:36:57,107
not long after opening the restaurants.

835
00:36:57,507 --> 00:37:00,707
Our restaurants have been on the list for four consecutive years.

836
00:37:01,877 --> 00:37:03,477
I studied Korean cuisine.

837
00:37:04,117 --> 00:37:06,047
My husband, Chef Yoon Dae Hyun,

838
00:37:06,587 --> 00:37:08,917
has experience in Western cuisine.

839
00:37:09,517 --> 00:37:12,256
Starting in Haebangchon, Yongsan,

840
00:37:12,257 --> 00:37:14,787
and all the way here, we've done all sorts of cooking.

841
00:37:14,987 --> 00:37:17,357
Making boxed lunches, catering buffets,

842
00:37:17,597 --> 00:37:19,227
serving canapés for brands,

843
00:37:19,327 --> 00:37:20,667
off-site cooking,

844
00:37:20,727 --> 00:37:22,096
and serving everything from gukbap to fine-dining dishes.

845
00:37:22,097 --> 00:37:23,637
We have experience in many fields.

846
00:37:24,367 --> 00:37:28,037
We want to prove that we can also cook...

847
00:37:28,237 --> 00:37:29,337
easy-to-understand casual food.

848
00:37:29,437 --> 00:37:33,176
People would've thought we'd cook Western food.

849
00:37:33,177 --> 00:37:34,306
That's the twist.

850
00:37:34,307 --> 00:37:36,817
- Like fine-dining dishes.
- You know.

851
00:37:37,017 --> 00:37:39,386
Plating with tweezers and such...

852
00:37:39,387 --> 00:37:40,686
won't work here.

853
00:37:40,687 --> 00:37:42,817
The menu we chose was...

854
00:37:43,287 --> 00:37:47,687
charcoal-grilled tteokgalbi plate made with Korean beef and pork.

855
00:37:48,427 --> 00:37:51,057
We wanted to serve a rice bowl...

856
00:37:51,327 --> 00:37:54,266
where you could enjoy tteokgalbi...

857
00:37:54,267 --> 00:37:56,537
without any other side dishes.

858
00:37:57,697 --> 00:38:00,637
The ingredient cost was a big concern.

859
00:38:01,567 --> 00:38:03,277
We went all in on the Korean beef and pork.

860
00:38:10,677 --> 00:38:12,287
The charcoal-grilled flavour.

861
00:38:12,687 --> 00:38:15,557
The charcoal-grilled flavour makes people go wild.

862
00:38:15,757 --> 00:38:19,627
The flavour of stove-grilled and charcoal-grilled food is different.

863
00:38:19,827 --> 00:38:21,997
Only when you also enjoy that flavour...

864
00:38:22,127 --> 00:38:24,297
will you think, "That was a great meal."

865
00:38:25,827 --> 00:38:28,797
Stir-fried cabbage that's like chilli pepper japchae.

866
00:38:28,867 --> 00:38:31,397
(Garlic puree)

867
00:38:31,867 --> 00:38:34,967
Stir-frying it with garlic puree to give it that smoky flavour.

868
00:38:39,047 --> 00:38:42,247
We thought it needed a visual shock.

869
00:38:44,117 --> 00:38:46,887
Our key element is burdock.

870
00:38:48,047 --> 00:38:49,687
The deep-fried burdock looks like fire.

871
00:38:49,857 --> 00:38:52,287
- What about it? That's good.
- It's golden.

872
00:38:54,027 --> 00:38:56,427
Remember how our concept is the movies?

873
00:38:56,997 --> 00:38:59,097
Truffle honey cheese popcorn.

874
00:38:59,327 --> 00:39:00,867
The customers will get a big serving of it.

875
00:39:01,367 --> 00:39:05,037
(Finishing it off with truffle powder)

876
00:39:06,507 --> 00:39:07,706
(Touching)

877
00:39:07,707 --> 00:39:09,237
- Is that real popcorn?
- Isn't that real?

878
00:39:09,637 --> 00:39:10,637
It is.

879
00:39:10,677 --> 00:39:12,477
(Interested)

880
00:39:13,107 --> 00:39:15,006
Look, Mom. They're giving out popcorn.

881
00:39:15,007 --> 00:39:16,117
- What?
- Popcorn.

882
00:39:16,747 --> 00:39:18,847
"Complimentary truffle honey popcorn."

883
00:39:19,587 --> 00:39:21,287
This one? Okay.

884
00:39:22,817 --> 00:39:23,917
Is that the screen?

885
00:39:24,817 --> 00:39:26,927
- Is that how they're cooking?
- It seems like it.

886
00:39:27,827 --> 00:39:29,257
Tteokgalbi also sounds nice.

887
00:39:31,357 --> 00:39:32,426
Honey, the tteokgalbi is...

888
00:39:32,427 --> 00:39:33,697
- blowing up.
- Nice.

889
00:39:34,467 --> 00:39:37,567
Families are bringing their children for dinner.

890
00:39:37,697 --> 00:39:40,767
Tteokgalbi must've been a good menu option to eat with the children.

891
00:39:42,507 --> 00:39:43,607
Let's get going now.

892
00:39:44,207 --> 00:39:45,237
Quickly.

893
00:39:46,107 --> 00:39:47,807
Quickly, chef.

894
00:39:48,477 --> 00:39:49,477
Quickly.

895
00:39:50,477 --> 00:39:52,886
(Extraordinary Couple)

896
00:39:52,887 --> 00:39:55,187
(Meanwhile, the restaurant next to Extraordinary Couple)

897
00:39:55,587 --> 00:39:56,917
The hamburger steak is the problem.

898
00:39:58,157 --> 00:39:59,187
The problem is the hamburger steak.

899
00:40:00,787 --> 00:40:02,057
Little did I think business would be this slow.

900
00:40:03,457 --> 00:40:06,427
(Wolfie's: Lunch sales, 13th place)

901
00:40:06,527 --> 00:40:10,666
Hi. I'm Lee Jae Hoon, Seochon's original good-vibes guy.

902
00:40:10,667 --> 00:40:11,697
Nice to meet you.

903
00:40:12,667 --> 00:40:15,807
Around ten years ago, there weren't many restaurants in Seochon.

904
00:40:17,037 --> 00:40:18,337
From what I saw,

905
00:40:18,777 --> 00:40:21,247
I thought I could create something from scratch.

906
00:40:21,507 --> 00:40:24,617
You could say I opened the first wine bar,

907
00:40:24,647 --> 00:40:27,317
hamburger steak specialty restaurant,

908
00:40:27,417 --> 00:40:29,587
and burger place in Seochon.

909
00:40:29,917 --> 00:40:32,887
After understanding the supply and demand flow,

910
00:40:33,557 --> 00:40:35,286
my restaurants continued to be fully booked...

911
00:40:35,287 --> 00:40:36,826
within just three days after opening.

912
00:40:36,827 --> 00:40:38,797
Lines were over 100m long.

913
00:40:39,567 --> 00:40:41,567
Those were all small restaurants.

914
00:40:41,627 --> 00:40:45,337
I doubt anyone has cooked in kitchens smaller than mine.

915
00:40:45,607 --> 00:40:48,876
We have to cook a dish with a limited selling price...

916
00:40:48,877 --> 00:40:49,977
in a small space.

917
00:40:50,307 --> 00:40:53,807
I had full confidence that my team would ace it.

918
00:40:56,277 --> 00:40:58,616
Hamburger steak with black bean rice.

919
00:40:58,617 --> 00:40:59,786
(Hamburger steak with black bean rice, 12.90 dollars)

920
00:40:59,787 --> 00:41:02,786
My teammate is Chef Kim Jin Gyo.

921
00:41:02,787 --> 00:41:04,816
We've been working together for 20 years.

922
00:41:04,817 --> 00:41:05,887
(Chef Kim Jin Gyo, Partners for 20 years)

923
00:41:06,687 --> 00:41:09,697
(What's the problem with the hamburger steak?)

924
00:41:11,597 --> 00:41:12,627
Oh, gosh.

925
00:41:13,427 --> 00:41:15,227
The couple wrote, "Michelin Star Couple."

926
00:41:16,237 --> 00:41:17,967
Isn't that foul play?

927
00:41:18,937 --> 00:41:23,107
The booth right next to us is Chef Hee Eun's.

928
00:41:23,337 --> 00:41:25,207
We are selling hamburger steak,

929
00:41:25,847 --> 00:41:27,746
while they are selling tteokgalbi.

930
00:41:27,747 --> 00:41:29,317
(A similar menu right next door)

931
00:41:29,477 --> 00:41:30,547
What are you feeling?

932
00:41:30,877 --> 00:41:32,747
- That place. Wolfie's.
- Wolfie's?

933
00:41:33,187 --> 00:41:35,687
"The Michelin couple's epic story."

934
00:41:35,817 --> 00:41:36,886
Wait. Charcoal-grilled tteokgalbi...

935
00:41:36,887 --> 00:41:38,317
- Tteokgalbi?
- rice plate?

936
00:41:39,327 --> 00:41:41,526
In a way, our menus are similar,

937
00:41:41,527 --> 00:41:43,657
both using ground meat...

938
00:41:44,397 --> 00:41:46,367
and cooking it.

939
00:41:47,127 --> 00:41:48,497
I felt uneasy.

940
00:41:49,167 --> 00:41:51,437
Wasn't their dish a bit fancier?

941
00:41:52,067 --> 00:41:53,966
Plus, theirs was three dollars more expensive.

942
00:41:53,967 --> 00:41:55,006
- Is that so?
- Theirs was three dollars...

943
00:41:55,007 --> 00:41:56,076
pricier.

944
00:41:56,077 --> 00:41:57,377
(Sulking)

945
00:41:58,777 --> 00:41:59,977
The hamburger steak isn't selling.

946
00:42:01,107 --> 00:42:03,777
What do we do? We need a countermeasure.

947
00:42:04,617 --> 00:42:06,647
Let's sell the rest at a discount.

948
00:42:07,787 --> 00:42:09,816
Since the lime chilli noodles were selling well,

949
00:42:09,817 --> 00:42:12,587
we had to find a way to sell the hamburger steak too.

950
00:42:12,727 --> 00:42:15,226
For dinner, it's going to be 10.90 dollars,

951
00:42:15,227 --> 00:42:16,257
a two-dollar difference.

952
00:42:16,327 --> 00:42:17,857
We decided to cut the price.

953
00:42:20,827 --> 00:42:23,767
It's 10.90 dollars. The price went down.

954
00:42:25,097 --> 00:42:26,437
Two hamburger steaks.

955
00:42:26,867 --> 00:42:28,706
- You'll cook three at once, yes?
- Yes.

956
00:42:28,707 --> 00:42:30,736
- I'll make the lime chilli noodles.
- Thanks.

957
00:42:30,737 --> 00:42:31,737
We had a few...

958
00:42:31,738 --> 00:42:33,206
- hamburger steak orders.
- Yes.

959
00:42:33,207 --> 00:42:34,207
It was quite different...

960
00:42:34,208 --> 00:42:36,017
- from the lunch business.
- Totally.

961
00:42:36,117 --> 00:42:37,177
We had a few orders.

962
00:42:37,577 --> 00:42:39,747
Yes, it's your hamburger steak order.

963
00:42:40,317 --> 00:42:41,547
Enjoy.

964
00:42:41,687 --> 00:42:42,687
(The sales are increasing.)

965
00:42:42,688 --> 00:42:45,686
Business picked up quite quickly at dinner.

966
00:42:45,687 --> 00:42:46,757
- For real.
- Right?

967
00:42:47,287 --> 00:42:49,757
Here's your order. Enjoy.

968
00:42:50,657 --> 00:42:51,927
I'll help you out after this one, Jin Gyo.

969
00:42:52,097 --> 00:42:53,127
- Okay.
- We're backed up.

970
00:42:54,197 --> 00:42:56,097
- It's fine. Take your time.
- Are you okay?

971
00:42:56,367 --> 00:42:57,766
Three black bean rice.

972
00:42:57,767 --> 00:42:59,936
I'll make it after these two orders.

973
00:42:59,937 --> 00:43:02,377
Two orders of tteokgalbi are done.

974
00:43:05,337 --> 00:43:08,647
We're currently serving the dishes at an average speed of six minutes.

975
00:43:09,247 --> 00:43:12,177
Gosh, the adrenaline is pumping.

976
00:43:13,447 --> 00:43:15,547
We need to make five orders, including the rest.

977
00:43:16,217 --> 00:43:17,786
- Are there no dessert places?
- Mine's done.

978
00:43:17,787 --> 00:43:18,787
There are no desserts.

979
00:43:18,857 --> 00:43:20,557
Is it already ready?

980
00:43:21,727 --> 00:43:23,757
Mom!

981
00:43:24,427 --> 00:43:25,527
Mom!

982
00:43:26,597 --> 00:43:29,037
(Mom picks up the tteokgalbi.)

983
00:43:30,837 --> 00:43:31,837
I see.

984
00:43:31,838 --> 00:43:32,907
(Impressed)

985
00:43:33,807 --> 00:43:35,106
(Amazed)

986
00:43:35,107 --> 00:43:36,277
- This one!
- Gosh.

987
00:43:37,177 --> 00:43:38,807
This tteokgalbi is fire.

988
00:43:39,547 --> 00:43:41,507
It's so juicy. Here.

989
00:43:44,417 --> 00:43:46,017
(Savouring it)

990
00:43:47,447 --> 00:43:48,686
It looks like a chocolate donut.

991
00:43:48,687 --> 00:43:49,687
- This dish?
- Yes.

992
00:43:49,887 --> 00:43:51,817
Try it. What do you think?

993
00:43:55,427 --> 00:43:56,827
- Here, try it.
- Is it good?

994
00:43:57,627 --> 00:43:58,926
(Glancing)

995
00:43:58,927 --> 00:44:00,997
Mom, I want to try that dish.

996
00:44:01,167 --> 00:44:03,096
It looks like a donut, but it's not a donut.

997
00:44:03,097 --> 00:44:04,767
This is tteokgalbi.

998
00:44:06,007 --> 00:44:07,267
Don't get shocked.

999
00:44:12,347 --> 00:44:13,847
Gosh, it's mind-blowing.

1000
00:44:15,447 --> 00:44:17,077
Something I've never tasted before.

1001
00:44:17,517 --> 00:44:19,617
- Is it a new experience?
- I mean the tteokgalbi.

1002
00:44:23,917 --> 00:44:24,917
(Impressed)

1003
00:44:25,927 --> 00:44:27,187
It's really tender.

1004
00:44:28,927 --> 00:44:29,927
Delicious.

1005
00:44:31,697 --> 00:44:32,766
Congratulations.

1006
00:44:32,767 --> 00:44:34,096
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

1007
00:44:34,097 --> 00:44:35,427
You're almost done!

1008
00:44:36,367 --> 00:44:37,567
Whatever.

1009
00:44:38,767 --> 00:44:41,567
(The next-door restaurant heard it.)

1010
00:44:42,477 --> 00:44:43,576
(Current Revenue: 961.60 dollars)

1011
00:44:43,577 --> 00:44:44,837
We don't have much left, Jin Gyo.

1012
00:44:45,907 --> 00:44:47,607
The ranking keeps changing.

1013
00:44:48,547 --> 00:44:49,617
Dinner.

1014
00:44:50,377 --> 00:44:51,447
I'm losing it.

1015
00:44:52,817 --> 00:44:55,087
"It's about time we're called."

1016
00:44:55,287 --> 00:44:56,417
"Where's the announcement?"

1017
00:44:57,257 --> 00:44:58,687
We need to keep the pace.

1018
00:44:59,487 --> 00:45:01,086
- We're doing well.
- No. Why are we faltering?

1019
00:45:01,087 --> 00:45:02,157
We won't falter.

1020
00:45:02,597 --> 00:45:05,527
I kept looking at the number of remaining tteokgalbi.

1021
00:45:06,797 --> 00:45:08,027
"We have eight left."

1022
00:45:08,997 --> 00:45:10,267
"We have six left."

1023
00:45:11,197 --> 00:45:12,567
- There aren't many left.
- Okay.

1024
00:45:12,837 --> 00:45:14,637
- We have four left.
- We're done.

1025
00:45:15,037 --> 00:45:16,877
- Really, I...
- Hang in there.

1026
00:45:18,377 --> 00:45:19,647
Just four more customers.

1027
00:45:22,007 --> 00:45:23,377
One is done, and three are left. Right?

1028
00:45:23,717 --> 00:45:24,717
Yes.

1029
00:45:24,718 --> 00:45:26,687
We've got 4 left. 4 hamburger steaks.

1030
00:45:27,087 --> 00:45:29,287
Our goal was to get into the top ten.

1031
00:45:29,917 --> 00:45:31,487
But even 11th place would be nice.

1032
00:45:33,887 --> 00:45:35,757
We now have...

1033
00:45:35,957 --> 00:45:38,827
the 11th restaurant to survive the 1,000-dollar sales race.

1034
00:45:39,427 --> 00:45:40,766
- It's not us, is it?
- The 11th restaurant...

1035
00:45:40,767 --> 00:45:41,797
to survive is...

1036
00:45:43,637 --> 00:45:45,937
(Which restaurant survived 11th?)

1037
00:45:46,367 --> 00:45:47,566
Extraordinary Couple.

1038
00:45:47,567 --> 00:45:48,736
(11th place: Extraordinary Couple by Kim Hee Eun, )

1039
00:45:48,737 --> 00:45:49,837
(Survived in 198 minutes)

1040
00:45:50,277 --> 00:45:51,307
We're going home!

1041
00:45:53,107 --> 00:45:54,447
Extraordinary Couple.

1042
00:45:56,877 --> 00:45:58,847
(Sighing)

1043
00:45:59,347 --> 00:46:01,247
When I heard...

1044
00:46:01,617 --> 00:46:04,187
Extraordinary Couple survived,

1045
00:46:05,187 --> 00:46:08,327
my stress level was almost at the max.

1046
00:46:08,857 --> 00:46:10,126
