1599
01:10:02,900 --> 01:10:05,629
An order for a medium bossam, makguksu, and rice balls.

1600
01:10:05,630 --> 01:10:06,630
Okay.

1601
01:10:06,700 --> 01:10:08,670
And one order for egg jangjorim rice balls.

1602
01:10:08,900 --> 01:10:10,600
- One?
- Yes. Make one.

1603
01:10:11,610 --> 01:10:14,440
(They continue to drive up the sales with their set meal strategy.)

1604
01:10:16,840 --> 01:10:20,280
We will close orders in ten minutes from now.

1605
01:10:22,450 --> 01:10:24,019
(10 minutes remaining)

1606
01:10:24,020 --> 01:10:25,450
This is the final stretch.

1607
01:10:26,220 --> 01:10:28,120
We need to execute our strategy now.

1608
01:10:28,320 --> 01:10:29,859
Buy tteokbokki and get fishcakes for free.

1609
01:10:29,860 --> 01:10:32,160
Buy fritters and get tteokbokki for free. What do you say?

1610
01:10:32,360 --> 01:10:34,099
We served a generous amount...

1611
01:10:34,100 --> 01:10:37,100
even to customers who ordered just one tteokbokki.

1612
01:10:37,500 --> 01:10:38,700
One tteokbokki.

1613
01:10:39,070 --> 01:10:41,800
Give them deep-fried shrimp or anything on the house.

1614
01:10:42,440 --> 01:10:44,370
It is a battle of total revenue, so they must sell as much as possible.

1615
01:10:44,470 --> 01:10:45,910
They have to sell as much as possible.

1616
01:10:46,770 --> 01:10:49,279
- Should we do a clearance sale?
- We should.

1617
01:10:49,280 --> 01:10:50,740
It's 38 dollars now,

1618
01:10:51,380 --> 01:10:54,650
so we can make it 28 dollars and include all the menu items.

1619
01:10:54,850 --> 01:10:56,950
- Makguksu and rice balls?
- Yes. Include everything.

1620
01:10:57,590 --> 01:10:59,489
This is our last chance. Let's go with a clearance sale.

1621
01:10:59,490 --> 01:11:01,290
(They slash the prices with only 10 minutes left.)

1622
01:11:01,720 --> 01:11:04,830
I'm still refusing to let go of the last shred of hope.

1623
01:11:07,760 --> 01:11:09,530
All right. Smoke is rising.

1624
01:11:09,900 --> 01:11:12,200
Let's go. Get one order out.

1625
01:11:12,500 --> 01:11:13,500
Okay.

1626
01:11:13,730 --> 01:11:14,900
Please.

1627
01:11:17,740 --> 01:11:19,739
There's no point in having leftovers.

1628
01:11:19,740 --> 01:11:21,680
We should give them a lot. I'm so grateful.

1629
01:11:21,980 --> 01:11:24,079
(To sell even one serving more, )

1630
01:11:24,080 --> 01:11:26,080
(they use their ultimate secret weapons.)

1631
01:11:26,280 --> 01:11:27,620
- This can be a strategy.
- What?

1632
01:11:27,920 --> 01:11:30,080
We should make them full so they won't order anything else.

1633
01:11:31,090 --> 01:11:33,420
(Sunlin burns up their energy until the very end.)

1634
01:11:41,460 --> 01:11:44,000
I really hope Chef Yoo Bang Nyeong will make it.

1635
01:11:45,630 --> 01:11:47,740
This is a huge plot twist.

1636
01:11:50,470 --> 01:11:51,839
There isn't much time left.

1637
01:11:51,840 --> 01:11:53,670
(Agungi)

1638
01:11:54,070 --> 01:11:55,240
Let's do this.

1639
01:11:55,980 --> 01:11:57,510
We should sell all of our remaining soup here.

1640
01:11:57,780 --> 01:11:59,910
We've sold nearly 60 portions today.

1641
01:12:00,710 --> 01:12:02,350
- They ordered one more?
- Yes.

1642
01:12:06,390 --> 01:12:07,520
